---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PrecisionVerifier from '../components/PrecisionVerifier.astro';
const sections = ['identities', 'tool', 'modes', 'methodology'];
---

<BaseLayout title="Precision Verifier — GCD" description="Verify kernel identities to machine precision across random, manual, and preset traces.">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">

    <!-- ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-2">Precision Verifier</h1>
      <p class="text-kernel-400 text-lg italic">Probatio per reditum — test by return.</p>
      <p class="text-kernel-500 text-sm mt-2 max-w-3xl">
        The kernel's three algebraic identities hold to machine precision for <em>every</em>
        valid trace vector. This tool lets you verify that claim directly — generate
        random traces, enter custom channels, explore structural presets, audit seam
        budgets, and compose subsystems. All computation runs client-side.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ═══════════ NAV ═══════════ -->
    <nav class="mb-8 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      {sections.map(s => (
        <a href={`#${s}`} class="px-3 py-1.5 rounded-full text-xs font-medium
          bg-kernel-800/60 text-kernel-400 hover:text-kernel-200 hover:bg-kernel-700/60
          border border-kernel-700/40 transition no-underline">
          {s.replace(/-/g, ' ').replace(/\b\w/g, c => c.toUpperCase())}
        </a>
      ))}
    </nav>

    <!-- ═══════════ §1: THE THREE IDENTITIES ═══════════ -->
    <section id="identities" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">The Three Algebraic Identities</h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-kernel-400 mb-4">
        These are not approximations or statistical claims. They are exact algebraic
        consequences of the kernel definition. Any trace vector that violates them
        indicates an implementation error, not a theoretical exception.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-green-700/30 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="text-green-400 font-bold text-lg mb-1">F + &omega; = 1</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-kernel-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Duality Identity</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Fidelity and drift are complementary — every unit of signal preserved
            is a unit not lost. Residual: exactly 0.0 across all traces.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-kernel-600 font-mono">complementum perfectum</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-amber-700/30 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="text-amber-400 font-bold text-lg mb-1">IC &le; F</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-kernel-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Integrity Bound</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Multiplicative coherence cannot exceed arithmetic mean. The solvability condition:
            c&#8321;,&#8322; = F &plusmn; &radic;(F&sup2; &minus; IC&sup2;) requires IC &le; F for real solutions.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-kernel-600 font-mono">limbus integritatis</div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900 border border-blue-700/30 rounded-lg p-4">
          <div class="text-blue-400 font-bold text-lg mb-1">IC = exp(&kappa;)</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-kernel-500 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">Log-Integrity Relation</div>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            The multiplicative coherence is exactly the exponential of the log-integrity.
            Links additive (&kappa;) and multiplicative (IC) measures of coherence.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-2 text-xs text-kernel-600 font-mono">integritas composita</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §2: INTERACTIVE TOOL ═══════════ -->
    <section id="tool" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Interactive Verifier</h2>
      <PrecisionVerifier />
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §3: VERIFICATION MODES ═══════════ -->
    <section id="modes" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Five Verification Modes</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">1. Random Trials</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Generate thousands of random trace vectors and verify all three identities
            across every one. Configure channel count and trial count. Reports max residual
            and pass/fail statistics.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">2. Manual Trace</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Enter channel values directly and see per-gate conformance in real time.
            Includes conformance guidance — the tool shows exactly which invariant
            failed and what would need to change.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">3. Preset Explorer</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Six structural presets (equator, near-zero, near-one, mixed, dead-channel,
            all-ones) plus 32 cross-domain entities. Click any preset to verify
            identities with known-good data.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">4. Seam Budget</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Interactive seam accounting: compute &Gamma;(&omega;), D_C (curvature debit),
            and &Delta;&kappa; (budget balance). Verify that the conservation budget
            &Delta;&kappa; = R&middot;&tau;_R &minus; (D_&omega; + D_C) closes within tolerance.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-2">5. Composition</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Compose two independent traces and verify the composition algebra:
            IC composes geometrically (IC&#8321;&#8322; = &radic;(IC&#8321;&middot;IC&#8322;)),
            F composes arithmetically (F&#8321;&#8322; = (F&#8321;+F&#8322;)/2).
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-200 mb-1">Why Five Modes?</h3>
          <p class="text-xs text-kernel-400">
            Each mode tests a different aspect of kernel correctness:
            algebraic identity, input sensitivity, domain specificity,
            seam closure, and compositional consistency. Together they
            cover the full verification surface.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══════════ §4: METHODOLOGY ═══════════ -->
    <section id="methodology" class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-kernel-100 mb-4">Verification Methodology</h2>
      <div class="bg-kernel-900/50 border border-kernel-800/40 rounded-xl p-5">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-xs text-kernel-400">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-300 mb-2">Precision Standard</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5">
              <li>&bull; <strong class="text-kernel-300">Machine epsilon:</strong> ~2.22 &times; 10&#8315;&#185;&#8310; (IEEE 754 double precision)</li>
              <li>&bull; <strong class="text-kernel-300">Guard band:</strong> &epsilon; = 10&#8315;&#8312; (frozen — prevents pole at &omega; = 1)</li>
              <li>&bull; <strong class="text-kernel-300">Seam tolerance:</strong> tol = 0.005 (frozen — width where IC &le; F holds at 100%)</li>
              <li>&bull; <strong class="text-kernel-300">F + &omega; = 1:</strong> exact to 0.0e+00 residual (not approximate — exactly zero)</li>
              <li>&bull; <strong class="text-kernel-300">IC = exp(&kappa;):</strong> residual &lt; 10&#8315;&#185;&#8310;</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-sm font-bold text-kernel-300 mb-2">What the Verifier Proves</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-1.5">
              <li>&bull; The browser's JavaScript engine reproduces the same identities as the Python test suite</li>
              <li>&bull; The frozen parameters (&epsilon;, p, &alpha;, tol) produce the same kernel outputs across implementations</li>
              <li>&bull; The three identities hold universally — no trace vector can violate them</li>
              <li>&bull; Composition algebra (geometric IC, arithmetic F) is exact</li>
              <li>&bull; This is the Cognitive Equalizer in action: same data + same contract = same verdict</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-4 pt-3 border-t border-kernel-800 text-xs text-kernel-500 italic text-center">
          Non agens mensurat, sed structura. — Not the agent measures, but the structure.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <div class="text-center text-kernel-600 text-xs italic pb-8">
      Numeri sunt intellectus. — The numbers are the understanding.
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
